metadata.name: contrapuntos #544
metadata.description:
Musical counterpoint is to me an abstraction of the layered, intertwining rhythms of every activity we carry on in our lives. With a global tempo typically set in days, we fit all sorts of temporal structures where our joys and fears live and play out over the span of our lives. This series is a metaphorical transposition of the musical counterpoint into a visual space, sometimes with repeating patterns, sometimes with broken structures, sometimes isolated notes / hours / souls.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodríguez, @msoriaro. Made with p5js & glsl.

metadata.name: Uninhabitable #76
metadata.description:
Uninhabitable is a generative system built only from ellipses. The process of playing with different geometric and trigonometric disruptions gives rise to four different compositions which seek to evoque living constructions and environments. Besides the shape itself and its related distortion, the stroke weight of the lines plays a meaningful role in the piece. Following a discrete range [0.01,0.1,1] the weight reveals the process allowing the viewer to realize the trace of the huge amount of lines in each piece. This back and forth between scales and context is, while kind of stripping the code, part of my continuing interest on understanding the -usually- crazy paths of machines' way of thinking.

Press "h" to see it and high resolution and refresh to get back to the initial state. Press "h" to save it.

Uninhabitable is an original work by Iskra Velitchkova. 2021.

metadata.name: Shattered Moons #329
metadata.description:
🌘🌗🌖Shattered Moons🌔🌓🌒

Explore deep space moons through this pure SVG generative experiment.

Features:
- Striped Background
- Shadows
- Vapors
- Horizontal Vapors
- Meteors
- Colored Meteors
- White Moon (0.5%)

SVG being a vectorial format, this work can be displayed/printed at any size.
Press 's' on Live View to save the SVG.
Press 'p' on Live View using a Chromium based browser to export as PNG.

Also, to fully enjoy your piece, I'd suggest to use a Chromium based browser as the SVG renderer gives more details.

metadata.name: Multidimensional Maximalism #116
metadata.description:
Multidimensional Maximalism is my learning experience with layering and composition.

Using the Cellular Automaton algorithm from "Gen., Machina" we create multiple dimensions of life. Each with it's own unique evolution and structure. Like petri dishes in a lab. We then use different compositional elements to explore these dimensions.

100% code - as always.

Available overlays
--
* Lasers (drawing inspiration from The Harvest by Per Kristian Stoveland)
* Circleblend
* Drops
* Lenses
* Squares
* Crazysquares
* Waves
* Tesseract (drawing inspiration from the awesome Tesseract collection by Studio Yorktown)
* None (unlucky you)

Controls (in live view):
--
Press [1-9] to set the export scale ratio
Press [s] to save a high resolution image [ resolution x scale ]

enjoy.

metadata.name: Lands #47
metadata.description:
Lands are a group of artworks creating a minimalist and abstract satellite view. The earth is changing, more and more, day after day, the satellite views are a great proof of that. Stay aware and be careful is important.

I wanted to representing something real, linked with my values, and keep a beautiful composition and colors harmony.  I worked with a new fresh touch for the colors management.

The size, position and frequency of the pieces are generated for each token, along with the color theme. 

Features : 
- piecesCount : the number of circles and rectangles.
- glitchLinesCount :  the number of lines behind the shapes.
- MultipleGlitchDirections : if the directions of the lines behind are just horizontal or vertical, or both (10% of chance to have only one direction) .

 Handmade by code with Javascript, made with fragment.tools
 Quentin Hocdé, Brussels (Belgium), 2023.

metadata.name: SquareCuts #39
metadata.description:
For my third project, a simple square is cut into small pieces that are rotated, moved or softened.
By playing on these parameters, we obtain many results with interesting aspects. Seven output families are possible.

Made with p5.js by Hervé

metadata.name: Brinco #81
metadata.description:
As slinkies rise and sway through flurries of confetti, sometimes this play is focused and orderly. At other times, they crowd together riotously, conspiring to sneak off the sides altogether.

"Brinco" (Portuguese for "I play") is about celebrating finding joy in my creative pursuits again; about not overthinking it and simply following what makes me happy.

Creative joy can be capricious, leaving us when we need it the most. We hope we can relate to our artistic practice in a positive way, tapping into what feels like a bottomless source of energy and excitement. But sometimes when life becomes overwhelming, what gave you energy before now feels hollow and rote—just one more thing sapping at you, and an emptiness where creative passion once resided.

For over a year, I've been sitting in this shadow. Until one day, I sat down and started tinkering… and for the first time in such a long time, I started to feel the spark.

I hope that viewers and collectors feel that same spark of joy and playfulness when seeing these pieces that I've felt creating them.

Press "s"/"S" to save a PNG at the current size and press "h"/"H" to save a high resolution version.

metadata.name: Monochrome Intersections #7
metadata.description:
I decided to do this version because Intersections created too many issues with the previews. I made a reserve list for all collectors of Intersections (this reserve list will be available during 1 week). I put a small price because of preview’s issues and I am really grateful to saw all my projects found collectors, and I don’t know how to tell you 🙏
 I also worked on a bug to fix the rendering on objkt.com. 

Monochrome Intersections are a group of artworks creating organic and animated lines. A mix between digital renderings with colorful lines and a generated grid creating a paper-like visual.

Lines are animated with an infinite algorithm to create a mesmerizing animation. 
The pieces's size, position and frequency are generated for each token, along with the colour theme and the composition effect. 

You can click to play/pause the animation.

Features :
- Clip: triangle, circle or reversed triangle
- LinesCount: number of lines
- smallLines: boolean, if lines are thin or bold
- colorTheme: name of the color theme
- filter: Canvas composition effect applied : difference, multiply, xor, hard-light, source-over
- isDistorted: distortions enabled

 Handmade by code with Javascript, made with fragment.tools
Quentin Hocdé, Brussels (Belgium), 2023.
